{% render 'partials/header-scroll.liquid', title: "Scroll Driven Animation" %}

    <main>
        <div class="scroll-bar"></div>

        <section class="main-content">
            <img src="../assets/img10.jpeg" alt="background image of buildings">
            <h1>Scroll driven animation</h1>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="background"></div> 
            <p>Scroll to explore more about scroll-driven animations and their use in modern web design. Learn how motion and interactivity can enhance the user experience.</p>
            <img class="image-container" src="../assets/img3.jpeg">
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="background"></div> 
            <p> Whether you're adding subtle movements or telling complete stories, scroll animations are a powerful tool in your design arsenal. Incorporating these animations can make your site unique and engaging.</p>
            <img class="image-container" src="../assets/img7.jpeg">
        </section>

        <section >
            <div class="background"></div>
            <h1 class="h1-code">Scroll-Driven Animation on images (CSS Only)</h1>
            <p class="p-code">To create a smooth scroll-driven animation on the image, I used CSS features like <code>animation-timeline</code> and <code>view()</code>, which allow animations to be triggered based on the scroll position. <code>Animation-timeline</code> triggers animation when the element enters the viewport. Here is the CSS used specifically for the images:</p>
            <pre>
                <code>
                    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
                        .image-container {
                            position: absolute;
                            top: 25%;
                            left: 25%;
                            width: 50vw;
                            height: 50vh;
                            animation: fade-in linear;
                            animation-timeline: view();   
                            animation-range: entry; 
                        }

                        @keyframes fade-in {
                            from {
                                scale: 0.7;
                                opacity: 0;
                            }

                            to {
                                scale: 1;
                                opacity: 1;
                            }
                        }
                    }

                </code>
            </pre>
        </section>

        <section>
            <div class="background"></div>
            <h1 class="h1-code">Sources Used</h1>
            <p class="p-code">While building this website, I relied on a few sources. Below is a list of the main resources I consulted:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://scroll-driven-animations.style/">Scroll-Driven-Animations</a>: For examples and explenation about scroll-driven animations.
                </li>

                <li>
                    <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5noL_qFobm0&list=PLNYkxOF6rcICM3ttukz9x5LCNOHfWBVnn">Youtube Chrome for developers</a>: For a playlist of Bramus van Damme explaining all about scroll-driven animations.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <article class="suggestions">            
                <h1>Suggestions for sroll driven animatons sources?</h1>
                <p>Do you have a useful resource for scroll-driven animations? Share your suggestion with us by leaving your name!*</p>
            </article>

            <form method="post" action="/scrolldriven">
                
                <h2>Name</h2>
                <input type="text" name="name" required/>

                <h2>Url</h2>
                <input type="text" name="description" required/>

                <button type="submit" id="submit-button" class="submit-button" >Submit</button>
            </form>
            
        </section>



       <section class="section-source">
            <div class="background"></div>
            <h1 class="h1-sources">Sended Sources</h1>
            {% for source in links reversed %} <!-- De nieuwste berichten als eerste worden getoond -->
                {% if forloop.index <= 4 %} <!-- Alleen objecten 1, 2 en 3 worden weergegeven -->
                    <p class="p-source-name">Name: {{ source.title }}</p> <!-- Hier wordt de naam weergegeven -->
                    <p class="p-source-url">URL: {{ source.url }}</p> <!-- Hier wordt de URL weergegeven -->
                {% else %}
                    {% break %} <!-- De rest van de berichten na object niet weergeven -->
                {% endif %}
            {% endfor %}
        </section>

        <script>
            let interactionSpinner = document.querySelector('#submit-button')

            interactionSpinner.addEventListener('click', rotate)

            function rotate () {
                interactionSpinner.classList.toggle('loader')
            }
        </script>
    </main>
    
    
</body>
</html>